method.name: IsInitialized
method.comment: Tests whether the object has been initialized.

method.name: _create
method.comment: Constructs a resource response with the given MIME type, character encoding, and input stream. MimeType As String - the resource response's MIME type, for example "text/html". Encoding As String - the resource response's character encoding, for example "utf-8". Data As InputStream - the input stream that provides the resource response's data. Added in API level 11.

method.name: _create2
method.comment: Constructs a resource response with the given parameters. MimeType As String - the resource response's MIME type, for example "text/html". Encoding As String - the resource response's character encoding, for example "utf-8". StatusCode As Int - the status code needs to be in the ranges [100, 299], [400, 599]. Causing a redirect by specifying a 3xx code is not supported. ReasonPhrase As String - the phrase describing the status code, for example "OK". Must be non-empty. This value cannot be null. ResponseHeaders As Map - the resource response's headers represented as a mapping of header name -> header value. Data As InputStream - the input stream that provides the resource response's data. Added in API level 21.

method.name: _getreasonphrase
method.comment: Gets the description of the resource response's status code. Added in API level 21.

method.name: _getstatuscode
method.comment: Gets the resource response's status code. Added in API level 21.

method.name: _initialize
method.comment: Initializes the object. AndroidWebkitWebResourceResponse As Object - android.webkit.WebResourceResponse from Java code. Pass Null if you want to create new instance. Use Create or Create2 methods to set new instance parameters. Added in API level 11.

method.name: _statuscodeandreasonphrase
method.comment: Sets the resource response's status code and reason phrase. StatusCode As Int - the status code needs to be in the ranges [100, 299], [400, 599]. Added in API level 21.
